Turkish Malls May Shift Rents to Lira from Dollar, Sabah Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-10-20T05:30:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/turkish-malls-may-shift-rents-to-lira-from-dollar-sabah-reports.html
As many as 20 Turkish shopping malls
may shift the rent they charge retailers into liras from dollars
after tenants complained at the fall in the value of the lira,
Sabah said.  Only malls that have no dollar-denominated debt are able to
make the shift, Istanbul-based Sabah said, citing Mehmet Nane,
head of the Association of Malls and Retailers.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
